cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper deals with machine learning and model interpretability, which are common topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically focuses on emotion recognition, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of Monte Carlo dropout and uncertainty measures also suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the identification of difficult and subjective training samples, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and social impact (cs.SI) research. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
